The paper focuses on learning social image embedding using deep models, which involves computer vision (CV) and multimedia (MM) analysis. The proposed approach also employs attention networks to encode the fine-granularity relation between image regions and textual words, which is related to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Additionally, the paper discusses the applications of multi-label classification and cross-modal search, which are relevant to machine learning (LG) and computational linguistics (CL).
